'''Between a Rock and a Hard Place''' is a [[phrase]] in the [[English language|English]] language meaning having to choose between two undesireable choices in certain situations.

==Origins==

This is an undated version of an expression dating back to the [[Ancient Greeks]], "between [[Scylla]] and [[Charybdis]]." The former was a large rock that endangered seaman in the [[Straits of Messina]], the latter was a potentially [[fatal]] [[whirlpool]] on the opposite side. [[Sailors]] tried to avoid sailing between them. It is speculated that Charybdis is known as "a hard place" partly because it's so hard to [[pronounce]] correctly.

